The paper deals with a channel model commonly used in wireless communication, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of multiple antennas and channel state information also suggests the possibility of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper addresses the fundamental limits of the channel model, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
